---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Pool Builders City of Casey | Full Council Service Area | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Concrete and fibreglass pool builders covering the full City of Casey - Berwick, Cranbourne, Narre Warren, Hampton Park, Endeavour Hills, Clyde, Hallam, Officer. AS 1926 compliance, reactive-clay engineering. VBA-registered."
  canonical="https://berwickpools.com.au/city-of-casey/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">City of Casey &middot; full council coverage</span>
      <h1>Pool builders across the <span class="accent">City of Casey</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Berwick in the centre, Cranbourne and Clyde to the south, Hampton Park
        and Hallam to the west, Endeavour Hills and Doveton to the north, Officer
        on the eastern boundary. We build concrete and fibreglass pools right
        across the council area - one council, one fence standard, one
        permit pathway we know cold.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free consultation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Full coverage</span>
      <h2>Suburbs we cover in Casey.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Featured suburb pages.</h3>
        <p>Detailed suburb-by-suburb guides - soil class, block size, typical specs, what we usually build.</p>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/endeavour-hills/">Endeavour Hills</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Other City of Casey suburbs.</h3>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Cranbourne East</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Cranbourne North</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Cranbourne West</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Cranbourne South</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Botanic Ridge</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Clyde</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Clyde North</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Hallam</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Doveton</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lyndhurst</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lynbrook</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Eumemmerring</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Beaconsfield</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Officer</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Narre Warren North</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Narre Warren South</span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Three zones, three design conversations.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Growth corridor</strong> (Cranbourne East/North/West, Clyde,
          Clyde North, Botanic Ridge, Officer): young families, new estate
          builds, 500-700m&sup2; blocks, Class M reactive soil, design
          covenants requiring glass or aluminium fencing. Fibreglass shells with
          travertine or porcelain paving are the default. Fast permit pathway
          - usually 4-6 weeks Council approval.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Established Casey</strong> (Berwick south, Narre Warren,
          Endeavour Hills, parts of Hampton Park): mature 70s-90s housing
          on 600-1,000m&sup2; blocks, mature gardens, sometimes
          access-challenged streets. Roughly even split between concrete and
          fibreglass depending on block constraints. Renovation work on
          original 80s and 90s pools is steady volume.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Rural-residential fringe</strong> (Hampton Park south, Hallam
          South Road, parts of Lyndhurst): 1,500-3,000m&sup2; blocks,
          mixed soil from Class M to Class H2, room for premium custom concrete
          pools 9-12m with feature walls, alfresco pavilions and full
          landscape integration. $90K-$140K builds are normal here.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">City of Casey permit checklist.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Building permit</strong> - every pool over 300mm deep. Council fee $560-$900 + private surveyor $1,800-$2,800.</li>
          <li><strong>Structural engineering certificate</strong> - reactive-clay piers, footings, reinforcement design. $1,200-$2,200.</li>
          <li><strong>Geotechnical soil report</strong> - needed for any concrete pool, recommended for fibreglass on H1+ sites. ~$700.</li>
          <li><strong>AS 1926.1-2012 fence certification</strong> - certified independent inspector. $400-$650.</li>
          <li><strong>Victorian pool register lodgement</strong> - mandatory within 30 days of completion. We handle it.</li>
          <li><strong>Domestic Building Insurance</strong> - required for any build over $16K. We carry it as a VBA-registered builder.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">All five services</span>
      <h2>What we build.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/new-concrete-pool/"><h3>New concrete pool</h3><p>$50K-$90K. Fully custom shotcrete shell, 50-year life.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/new-fibreglass-pool/"><h3>New fibreglass pool</h3><p>$35K-$60K. Australian-made shell, 25-year structural warranty.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/plunge-pool/"><h3>Plunge pool</h3><p>$25K-$45K. 3-5m compact, heat-pump-friendly, year-round.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/pool-renovation/"><h3>Pool renovation</h3><p>$8K-$30K. Resurface, retile, replumb, re-equip 90s pools.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/pool-equipment/"><h3>Pool equipment</h3><p>$1.5K-$8K. Pumps, filters, heat pumps, chlorinators, automation.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free consultation anywhere in the City of Casey.</h2>
        <p>One council, one permit pathway, one fence standard. We know all three. Fixed quote in 7-10 days.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
